    {
      "id": "el_96",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1005,
      "y": 2426,
      "width": 224,
      "height": 245,
      "text": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: Room=120m², Tile=0.25m²\nStep 2: Tiles = 120/0.25 = 480\n  Cost = 480×25 = Rs.12000\n\nTRICK:\nCount tiles per side:\n15/0.5 × 8/0.5 = 30×16 = 480\n(convert units first!)\n\n  ┌──── 15m ────┐\n  │ □□□□□□...   │ 8m\n  │ 30 × 16     │\n  └─────────────┘\n  Tile=0.5m → 480 tiles\n\nAnswer: 480 tiles, Rs.12000 ✓",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 12,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
